questions.explanation:
According to Charles law, At constant pressure, the volume of a given mass of a gas increases or decreases by $\frac{1}{273}$ of its volume at 0^oC for each one-degree rise or fall in temperature. Therefore at constant pressure, volume of given mass of gas is directly proportional to absolute temperature.
Mathematically; 
$V\,=kT$ (at contant P)

